# Configuration for running the GitHub Actions workflows locally with
# nektos/act (https://github.com/nektos/act). Used as a stopgap for CI until the
# repository is public (free Actions) or Actions billing is enabled.
#
# `act` runs ci.yml (the lightweight native checks: host build + unit tests incl.
# the function-prefix logic + registry validation) end-to-end in a stock
# container — no wasm toolchain, ~a minute. The heavy wasm smoke (smoke-tests.yml:
# lean core + ~180 components via tooling/smoke.py --all) is GitHub-runner only;
# run it locally with `python3 tooling/smoke.py --all`.
#
# Default to the lightweight workflow so `act` is fast + self-contained:
-W .github/workflows/ci.yml

# Map GitHub's `ubuntu-latest` to a runner image that ships apt/curl/git/node.
-P ubuntu-latest=catthehacker/ubuntu:act-latest

# Keep cargo/apt caches between runs.
--reuse
